    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok i get that the supreme court decides the law, but even then, laws change based on who is in charge. so if we look at the actual facts, like if strict laws stop people from killing each other or not... doesnt that matter more than how a judge feels about a sentence? like if the data shows it works, isn't it kind of dangerous to ignore that just because of a legal debate?",
